Solving to the problems I'm facing. 

Since launch, I got 100's of influencers , marketers and shilers reaching out to get a deal.

But without any way to track who's real and who's a scammer, neither a way to track the actual impact of such offers, how can builders know who to trust?

There needs to be a way to 
Curate influencers.
rate them
Measure their impact
Allocate resources based on contribution

Does anything like this exist ?

This is how I'm thinking about growing <> Building lifecycle for @ProductClank

Our #1 goal is to grow attention to the product, eating our own dog food by launching it first on the platform ($PRO) - if it works for us - it will work for anyone !

Our target audience:
Product Builders on one side
Traders / degens / speculators on the other

1. We experiment with growth hacks & tools that help us grow an audience
2. We evaluate and decide if that was a good use of our money/efforts
3. We integrate every tactic that does well into the product, so every product launching on ProductClank can easily do that

Every functionality integrated into the app will also have  integration built in

Feedback and growth hacks ideas are welcome !

text:
Testimonials from the Reddit rabbit hole

As i browse in various Reddit's communities - indie hackers, solo entrepreneur, builders, and SaaS products groups I find a lot of cool side projects, that may not fall into a "product" or a serious company category we may think of, but are sure a product of someone putting a few hours/days/weeks/months of work and coming up with something.

It's the geek equivalent of creating a cool video on Tiktok. It's creation. and somebody, somewhere, may find it to be really useful.  

Wouldn't it be cool if those products did not end up as a website nobody knows about, and instead gained a new phase in life where they are being tokenized into product coins, and then getting a chance to become something ? 

Anyone that runs into them can bet on the product, start promoting it, or build an extension or feature to that product, and revive it. next step could be integrate @splits into the product revenue stream.

Here's a simple, cool example I found:

https://parodyprints.com/
